  "prompt": "What universities for MS in CS should be considered with GRE - 317/340, CGPA - 9.15/10 and TOEFL - 102?",
  "response": "With a GRE score of 317, CGPA of 9.15/10, and TOEFL score of 102, you have a competitive profile for admissions to many prestigious universities for an MS in Computer Science. Here are some universities you might consider:\n\n### United States:\n1. **University of California, Berkeley** - Their MS in Computer Science is highly competitive, but your profile is strong.\n2. **Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT)** - Another highly competitive program.\n3. **Stanford University** - Known for its excellent CS program.\n4. **Carnegie Mellon University** - Renowned for computer science and engineering.\n5. **University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign** - Strong program with a good reputation.\n6. **University of Texas at Austin** - Offers a robust CS curriculum.\n7. **University of Southern California** - Offers good research opportunities.\n8. **University of Michigan, Ann Arbor** - Excellent CS program.\n9. **Georgia Institute of Technology** - Known for its strong technical programs.\n10. **University of Washington** - Seattle has a strong tech industry presence.\n\n### Canada:\n1. **University of Toronto** - One of Canada's top universities.\n2. **University of British Columbia** - Strong research facility.\n3. **McGill University** - Known for its rigorous academic programs.\n4. **University of Waterloo** - Widely recognized for its CS program.\n\n### Europe:\n1. **ETH Zurich (Switzerland)** - Prestigious university for science and technology.\n2. **Technical University of Munich (Germany)** - Strong CS program.\n3. **University of Cambridge (UK)** - Competitive but well-regarded program.\n4. **University of Oxford (UK)** - Prestigious with strong research opportunities.\n\n### Asia:\n1. **National University of Singapore** - Top-tier university with strong CS programs.\n2. **University of Hong Kong** - Offers good engineering and CS programs.\n3. **Tsinghua University (China)** - One of the most prestigious universities in China.\n\nNote that admission to these programs depends on a holistic review of your application, including letters of recommendation, statement of purpose, relevant research or work experience, and extracurricular involvement. Make sure to tailor your application materials to highlight your strengths and align them with the specific program and research interests of these institutions.",
